author: Steve DelVecchio
title: Washington's Jackson suffers injury setback in practice
text:
Washington's Jackson suffers injury setback in practice Larry Brown Sports 5 hrs ago Steve DelVecchio © Rob Carr/Getty Images DeSean Jackson suffered a setback with his hamstring injury. Washington Redskins wide receiver DeSean Jackson suffered a hamstring injury in his team’s Week 1 loss to the Miami Dolphins, and it would appear it is still bothering him more than a month later.
AdChoices Jackson has practiced on a limited basis this week, but he suffered a setback on Thursday.
Gruden said DJackson had twinge after going out for deep ball today; took himself out of practice and stayed out. Still hopeful Sun return
— Liz Clarke (@lizclarketweet) October 15, 2015
As Rotoworld notes , that is the same way Jackson hurt the hamstring in the first place. He claims he is still optimistic about playing Sunday against the New York Jets, but even a little “twinge” has to be very discouraging at this point.
